      },
      "date": "2017-11-25 09:46:05.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(2 comments)\n\nWhat are the compatibility implications of this change?  It isn't clear from the patch description whether this change is only in memory, or affects the on-disk LMM also?  Clearly, existing striped directories will not have the FIDs in the LMM (unless this is only on the generated LMM, not on disk).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
